# Airo Science Kit v1 — Schematic Reference
# KiCad 8 — schematic file lives at hardware/schematic/airo-science-kit-v1.kicad_sch
#
# This file documents all connections for reference and KiCad recreation.
# Use KiCad 8 (free download: https://www.kicad.org) to open the .kicad_sch file.

==============================================================
NET LIST — ALL CONNECTIONS
==============================================================

POWER RAILS
-----------
VBAT  : BT1(+)  → SW1(pin1)
3V3   : SW1(pin2) → XIAO(3V3) → C1(+)
GND   : BT1(-)  → XIAO(GND)  → C1(-) → C2(-) → R6(bot) → R7(bot)
5V    : XIAO(5V/VBUS) → C2(+)   [USB power only, not battery]

LED OUTPUTS  (GP0–GP4, Digital OUT, 3.3V logic)
-----------
GP0 → R1(top) → R1(bot) → LED1(A) → LED1(K) → GND   [Red]
GP1 → R2(top) → R2(bot) → LED2(A) → LED2(K) → GND   [Green]
GP2 → R3(top) → R3(bot) → LED3(A) → LED3(K) → GND   [Yellow]
GP3 → R4(top) → R4(bot) → LED4(A) → LED4(K) → GND   [Blue]
GP4 → R5(top) → R5(bot) → LED5(A) → LED5(K) → GND   [White]

BUZZER OUTPUT  (GP5, PWM OUT)
--------------
GP5  → BZ1(+)
GND  → BZ1(-)

BUTTON INPUTS  (GP6–GP9, Digital IN, internal pull-up)
--------------
GP6  → BTN1(pin1);  BTN1(pin2) → GND   [Button A]
GP7  → BTN2(pin1);  BTN2(pin2) → GND   [Button B]
GP8  → BTN3(pin1);  BTN3(pin2) → GND   [Button C]
GP9  → BTN4(pin1);  BTN4(pin2) → GND   [Button D]
Note: Enable internal pull-ups in firmware. Buttons are active-LOW.

SENSOR INPUTS  (GP26 = ADC0, GP27 = ADC1)
--------------
LDR voltage divider:
  3V3 → LDR1(top) → LDR1(bot) → node_A → R6 → GND
  node_A → GP26 (ADC0)

Thermistor voltage divider:
  3V3 → NTC1(top) → NTC1(bot) → node_B → R7 → GND
  node_B → GP27 (ADC1)

Note: Both dividers are top-variable (sensor on top, 10K fixed on bottom).
ADC reads voltage at mid-point. Higher light = lower LDR resistance = higher ADC.
Higher temp = lower NTC resistance = higher ADC.

DECOUPLING CAPACITORS
---------------------
C1: 3V3 to GND — place within 5mm of XIAO 3V3 pin
C2: 5V  to GND — place within 5mm of XIAO VBUS pin

XIAO RP2040 MODULE HEADERS
---------------------------
Left header  (H1, 7-pin female, 2.54mm):
  Pin 1: GP0
  Pin 2: GP1
  Pin 3: GP2
  Pin 4: GP3
  Pin 5: GP4
  Pin 6: GP5
  Pin 7: GP6

Right header (H2, 7-pin female, 2.54mm):
  Pin 1: GP27
  Pin 2: GP26
  Pin 3: GND
  Pin 4: 3V3
  Pin 5: GP9
  Pin 6: GP8
  Pin 7: GP7

==============================================================
PCB ZONE PLACEMENT GUIDE
==============================================================

Board size: 150mm × 150mm, 2-layer FR4, HASL or ENIG finish
Corner radius: 3mm (rounded for safety)
Silkscreen: White on green or blue soldermask

Zone A — Brain (top-left quadrant, ~75x75mm)
  - H1, H2 female headers (XIAO mounts here)
  - SW1 slide switch at board edge
  - C1, C2 decoupling caps close to XIAO
  - Silkscreen: "BRAIN" label, USB-C arrow pointing to board edge

Zone B — Output (top-right quadrant, ~75x75mm)
  - LED1–LED5 in a horizontal row, 10mm spacing
  - R1–R5 directly behind each LED
  - BZ1 buzzer with musical note silkscreen icon
  - Silkscreen: "OUTPUT" label, LED color dots under each LED

Zone C — Input (bottom half, full width, ~150x75mm)
  - BTN1–BTN4 evenly spaced, large silkscreen labels A B C D
  - Extra spacing for student fingers
  - Silkscreen: "INPUT" label

Zone D — Sense (right side of Zone B area)
  - LDR1 in a window cutout or near board edge for light exposure
  - NTC1 exposed (no covering component)
  - R6, R7 voltage dividers directly adjacent
  - Silkscreen: "LIGHT" and "TEMP" labels with icons

Battery holder:
  - BT1 on PCB underside or with JST connector at board edge
  - SW1 on top side at board edge for easy access

==============================================================
DESIGN RULES (JLCPCB compatible)
==============================================================
Min trace width    : 0.2mm (use 0.3mm for signal, 0.5mm for power)
Min clearance      : 0.2mm
Min drill size     : 0.3mm
Via size           : 0.8mm drill, 1.2mm pad
Copper pour        : GND fill on both layers
Soldermask         : Both sides
Silkscreen         : Both sides (labels on top)
